<br>
The Justice Dept. and ATF hate the bill. They are currently do everything, including illegal lobbying, to stop it. We know they are planning some kind of media event demonstrating the potential misuse of rockets using items they purchased from vendors. They have been trying to plant stories in major newspapers alleging that model rockets can be used to launch terrorist attacks against crowds in stadiums. They are calling staffers and members of Congress. The Senator from Alabama who told Homer Hickam that he was going to consponsor, back out after receiving &quot;arm twisting&quot; from the ATF. He was embarrassed to tell Senate Enzi and rather sheepishly apologized for backing out. Sen. Enzi was very angry at the illegal tactics used by the ATF. We have tried to get evidence on all of this, but staffers have not been successful to date. As I said in an earlier post, we are entering or in the &quot;hardball&quot; phase.<br>
<br>
The ATF and Justice Dept. people told Enzi's staffers that rocketry needs to be tightly controlled and regulated as it is a threat to Homeland Security. They see rockets as something that can be used to dispense chemical or biological agents over crowds. They also mentioned the idea of shooting down airplanes, but lately seemed more focused on the dispersion of chemicals or biological agents. Hence, they do not care about the propellant used to get the rocket up, only with payload capacity.<br>
<br>
John Wickman <br>
<br>
[ reposted by iz ]<br>
<br>
in Tom Clancy's bestseller &quot;Rainbow Six&quot;, chapter 33 - &quot;The Games Begin&quot; (paperback pp.739-741) he describes a plot to disperse biological agents through a cooling system at a stadium during the Olympic games. Everyone infected would carry the contagion to their home countries.<br>
<br>
I think Homeland Security would do better to deal with the creation and import of biolgical and chemical agents, than to the means of dispersal, where there are as many means as the imagine can concieve.<br>
